race.comment: VAN ROY (8) went forward and proved too strong last time out, scoring with plenty in hand over a similar trip at Penola. Backs up quickly and gets in light with slight rise in grade. Can make it two on the trot. KHOR (5) wasn't far away last time out, finishing fourth over 1700m at Warrnambool. The extra journey should play into his hands and he strips fitter third-up. Can play a major role. SURFY PETE (12) was in red-hot form to kick off the prep with back-to-back wins, and has since placed twice. Is drawn to get the gun run from the inside under the light weight and can feature once more. DARTBOARD (7) struggled last time in town but his two runs prior were good. Backs up quickly and reunites with Hill, who knows him well. Can bounce back sharply.
